data: 2016-cohort

# file.copy("/Users/nodashouhei/R/20240802_WRFS_Omi_mark-recapture/output/rawdata_filtered.csv","./input_data/rawdata_filtered.csv")

# AIC and BIC list
aic_bic <- data.frame(clu = c(),
                      aic = c(),
                      bic = c())

2 Estimation of growth trajectries using the finite mixture model

2.1 no. of cluster = 2

# number of k
kk <- 2

# output name
csv_name <- paste("./output/k", kk, "_data.csv", sep = "")

# read data
data <- read.csv("input_data/rawdata_filtered.csv")

# filtering
# remove individuals only captured once
data <- data %>%
  filter(cohort == 2016,
         treatment == 'early' | treatment == 'late' | treatment == 'control')

## von bertalanffy growth model ----------------------------------------------
sbgm <- function(lmax,lmin,a1,theta,t0=0,t){
  (lt <- lmax-(lmax-lmin)*exp(-a1*(t-t0)-180*a1/pi*(cos(pi*(t0+theta)/180)-cos(pi*(t+theta)/180))))
}

# functions
llsbgm <- function(para,data){
  lmax <- exp(para[1])
  lmin <- exp(para[2])
  a1 <- exp(para[3])
  theta <- para[4]
  t <- data[,1]
  lobs <- data[,2]
  ll <- -log(dnorm(log(lobs),log(sbgm(lmax,lmin,a1,theta,t=t)),sd=sd(log(lobs))))
  sum(ll)
}

llsbgm2 <- function(para,data){
  lmax <- exp(para[1])
  lmin <- exp(para[2])
  a1 <- exp(para[3])
  theta <- para[4]
  t <- data[,1]
  lobs <- data[,2]
  ll <- -log(dnorm(log(lobs),log(sbgm(lmax,lmin,a1,theta,t=t)),sd=sd(log(lobs))))
  ll
}

ipara <- c(log(max(data$fl)),log(min(data$fl)),log(1.7E-4),0)

lmax <- exp(ipara[1])
lmin <- exp(ipara[2])
a1 <- exp(ipara[3])
theta <- ipara[4]

t <- seq(0,max(data$days_from_hatching),by=1)

llsbgm(ipara,data[,c("days_from_hatching","fl")])
## [1] 1250.237
summary(llsbgm2(ipara,data[,c("days_from_hatching","fl")]))
##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
## -0.3488  0.1830  0.9456  1.1663  1.8904  6.9642
# single cluster (Models that do not assume growth classes)
res <- optim(ipara,llsbgm,data=data[,c("days_from_hatching","fl")])

#AIC
sum(res$value)+2*5
## [1] -202.4451
#BIC
sum(res$value)+5*log(nrow(data))
## [1] -177.5587
lmax <- exp(res$par[1])
lmin <- exp(res$par[2])
a1 <- exp(res$par[3])
theta <- res$par[4]

# plot
plot(t,sbgm(lmax,lmin,a1,theta,t=t), type="l", lwd = 3, ylim=c(0,max(data$fl)), 
     font.lab=1,
     xlab="No. of days since January-1",ylab="Fork length (mm)",
     cex.lab=1.5, cex.axis=1, las=1)
points(fl~days_from_hatching,data=data,
       cex=0.8, col=rgb(0, 0, 0,alpha=0.5))

data$predfl <- sbgm(lmax,lmin,a1,theta,t=data$days_from_hatching)
data$resid <- log(data$fl)-log(data$predfl)

# model
m1 <- FLXMRglm(resid~1,family="gaussian")

set.seed(1)

mp2 <- flexmix(.~.|id, data=data, model=list(m1), k=kk, 
               control=list(iter=200,minprior=0,nrep=3,classify="random"))

# show summary
summary(mp2)
## 
## Call:
## flexmix(formula = . ~ . | id, data = data, k = kk, model = list(m1), 
##     control = list(iter = 200, minprior = 0, nrep = 3, classify = "random"))
## 
##        prior size post>0 ratio
## Comp.1 0.509  559    904 0.618
## Comp.2 0.491  513    911 0.563
## 
## 'log Lik.' 664.9546 (df=5)
## AIC: -1319.909   BIC: -1295.023
data$cluster <- clusters(mp2)

k <- sort(unique(data$cluster))

ipara <- res$par
uid <- sort(unique(data$id))

ll <- as.numeric()
oll <- 1
set.seed(1)
while(abs(sum(ll)-sum(oll))>0.1){
  # M step
  oll <- ll
  ll <- as.numeric()
  estpara <- as.numeric()
  for(cl in k){
    res <- optim(ipara,llsbgm,data=data[data$cluster==cl,c("days_from_hatching","fl")])
    estpara <- rbind(estpara,res$par)
    data[,paste("ll",cl,sep="-")]<- llsbgm2(res$par,data[,c("days_from_hatching","fl")])
    ll <- c(ll,res$value)
  }
}
data$ocluster <- data$cluster
# E step
for(cid in uid){
  dmy <- data[data$id==cid,]
  cll <- apply(dmy[,paste("ll",k,sep="-")],2,sum)
  data[data$id==cid,]$cluster <- which(cll==min(cll))
}
print(c(sum(ll),sum(oll)))
## [1] -362.2538 -362.2538
data$ocluster <- data$cluster

#AIC
aic <- sum(ll)+2*max(k)*5
#BIC
bic <- sum(ll)+max(k)*5*log(nrow(data))

# make new data frame
add_data <- data.frame(clu = kk,
                       aic = aic,
                       bic = bic)
aic_bic <- rbind(aic_bic, add_data)

# sorting
par(mfrow=c(1,max(k)))

# make new data frame
ocluster <- c()
max_len <- c()
clu_max_len <- data.frame(ocluster,max_len)

for(ocluster in k){
  tmp = data[data$ocluster==ocluster,]
  tmp = tmp[tmp$days_from_hatching<300,]
  max_len = max(tmp$fl)
  # make new data frame
  add_data <- data.frame(ocluster, max_len)
  clu_max_len <- rbind(clu_max_len, add_data)
}


# sort by max length
clu_max_len <- clu_max_len[order(clu_max_len$max_len, decreasing=T),]
# create a sequential list
x <- 1:kk
# make new data frame
add_data <- data.frame(x)
names(add_data) <- c("ocluster_rename")
# bind
clu_max_len <- cbind(clu_max_len, add_data)
# merge
data <- left_join(data, clu_max_len, by=c("ocluster"="ocluster"))

# Change the order of the growth curves
# merge a sequential list
estpara2 <- cbind(estpara, x)
# make new data frame
estpara2 <- data.frame(estpara2)
# merge
estpara2 <- left_join(estpara2, clu_max_len, by=c("x"="ocluster"))
# sort
estpara2 <- estpara2[order(estpara2$ocluster_rename),]
# remove columns
estpara2 <- estpara2[,-5]
# convert matrix
estpara2 <- matrix(as.matrix(estpara2), nrow(estpara2), ncol(estpara2))

### plot growth history
kkk <- max(k)
if (max(k) == kk) {
  num_lis <- seq(1,kk,1)
} else {
  num_lis <- seq(1,kkk,1)
}

# plot
# color list
cb = brewer.pal(4, "RdYlBu")
cb = c("#D7191C","#2C7BB6")

g <- ggplot(NULL)
for(i in num_lis) {
  # data
  growth_curve <- tibble(
    t = t,
    fl = sbgm(exp(estpara2[i,1]), 
              exp(estpara2[i,2]), 
              exp(estpara2[i,3]), 
              estpara2[i,4], 
              t=t))
  # plot
  g <- g +
    geom_point(data = data[data$ocluster_rename==i,],
               aes(x = days_from_hatching, y = fl), 
               size = 2, alpha = 0.5, fill = cb[i],
               shape = 21, colour = "black") +
    geom_line(data = growth_curve, aes(x = t, y = fl),
              linewidth = 2, alpha=1, col = cb[i]) +
    labs(title = paste0(as.character(i), " clusters"), 
         x = "No. of days since January-1", 
         y = "Fork length (mm)")
}
g

# out to csv
data2 <- aggregate(ocluster_rename~id,data,unique)
write.csv(data2,csv_name, row.names = FALSE)

count(data2, ocluster_rename)
##   ocluster_rename   n
## 1               1 189
## 2               2 169

    fl = sbgm(exp(estpara2[i,1]), 
              exp(estpara2[i,2]), 
              exp(estpara2[i,3]), 
              estpara2[i,4], 
              t=t))
  # plot
  g <- g +
    geom_point(data = data[data$ocluster_rename==i,],
               aes(x = days_from_hatching, y = fl), 
               size = 2, alpha = 0.5, fill = cb[i],
               shape = 21, colour = "black") +
    geom_line(data = growth_curve, aes(x = t, y = fl),
              linewidth = 2, alpha=1, col = cb[i]) +
    labs(title = paste0(as.character(i), " clusters"), 
         x = "No. of days since January-1", 
         y = "Fork length (mm)")
}
g

# out to csv

write.csv(data2,csv_name, row.names = FALSE)

2.4 no. of cluster = 5

# number of k
kk <- 5

# output name
csv_name <- paste("./output/k", kk, "_data.csv", sep = "")

# read data
data <- read.csv("input_data/rawdata_filtered.csv")

# filtering
# remove individuals only captured once
data <- data %>%
  filter(cohort == 2016,
         treatment == 'early' | treatment == 'late' | treatment == 'control')

## von bertalanffy growth model ----------------------------------------------
sbgm <- function(lmax,lmin,a1,theta,t0=0,t){
  (lt <- lmax-(lmax-lmin)*exp(-a1*(t-t0)-180*a1/pi*(cos(pi*(t0+theta)/180)-cos(pi*(t+theta)/180))))
}

# functions
llsbgm <- function(para,data){
  lmax <- exp(para[1])
  lmin <- exp(para[2])
  a1 <- exp(para[3])
  theta <- para[4]
  t <- data[,1]
  lobs <- data[,2]
  ll <- -log(dnorm(log(lobs),log(sbgm(lmax,lmin,a1,theta,t=t)),sd=sd(log(lobs))))
  sum(ll)
}

llsbgm2 <- function(para,data){
  lmax <- exp(para[1])
  lmin <- exp(para[2])
  a1 <- exp(para[3])
  theta <- para[4]
  t <- data[,1]
  lobs <- data[,2]
  ll <- -log(dnorm(log(lobs),log(sbgm(lmax,lmin,a1,theta,t=t)),sd=sd(log(lobs))))
  ll
}

ipara <- c(log(max(data$fl)),log(min(data$fl)),log(1.7E-4),0)

lmax <- exp(ipara[1])
lmin <- exp(ipara[2])
a1 <- exp(ipara[3])
theta <- ipara[4]

t <- seq(0,max(data$days_from_hatching),by=1)

llsbgm(ipara,data[,c("days_from_hatching","fl")])
## [1] 1250.237
summary(llsbgm2(ipara,data[,c("days_from_hatching","fl")]))
##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
## -0.3488  0.1830  0.9456  1.1663  1.8904  6.9642
# single cluster (Models that do not assume growth classes)
res <- optim(ipara,llsbgm,data=data[,c("days_from_hatching","fl")])

#AIC
sum(res$value)+2*5
## [1] -202.4451
#BIC
sum(res$value)+5*log(nrow(data))
## [1] -177.5587
lmax <- exp(res$par[1])
lmin <- exp(res$par[2])
a1 <- exp(res$par[3])
theta <- res$par[4]

# plot
plot(t,sbgm(lmax,lmin,a1,theta,t=t), type="l", lwd = 3, ylim=c(0,max(data$fl)), 
     font.lab=1,
     xlab="No. of days since January-1",ylab="Fork length (mm)",
     cex.lab=1.5, cex.axis=1, las=1)
points(fl~days_from_hatching,data=data,
       cex=0.8, col=rgb(0, 0, 0,alpha=0.5))

data$predfl <- sbgm(lmax,lmin,a1,theta,t=data$days_from_hatching)
data$resid <- log(data$fl)-log(data$predfl)

# model
m1 <- FLXMRglm(resid~1,family="gaussian")

set.seed(1)

mp2 <- flexmix(.~.|id, data=data, model=list(m1), k=kk, 
               control=list(iter=200,minprior=0,nrep=3,classify="random"))

# show summary
summary(mp2)
## 
## Call:
## flexmix(formula = . ~ . | id, data = data, k = kk, model = list(m1), 
##     control = list(iter = 200, minprior = 0, nrep = 3, classify = "random"))
## 
##        prior size post>0 ratio
## Comp.1 0.212  262    801 0.327
## Comp.2 0.176  194    523 0.371
## Comp.3 0.306  333    812 0.410
## Comp.4 0.175  174    617 0.282
## Comp.5 0.131  109    689 0.158
## 
## 'log Lik.' 790.7784 (df=14)
## AIC: -1553.557   BIC: -1483.875
data$cluster <- clusters(mp2)

k <- sort(unique(data$cluster))

ipara <- res$par
uid <- sort(unique(data$id))

ll <- as.numeric()
oll <- 1
set.seed(1)
while(abs(sum(ll)-sum(oll))>0.1){
  # M step
  oll <- ll
  ll <- as.numeric()
  estpara <- as.numeric()
  for(cl in k){
    res <- optim(ipara,llsbgm,data=data[data$cluster==cl,c("days_from_hatching","fl")])
    estpara <- rbind(estpara,res$par)
    data[,paste("ll",cl,sep="-")]<- llsbgm2(res$par,data[,c("days_from_hatching","fl")])
    ll <- c(ll,res$value)
  }
}
data$ocluster <- data$cluster
# E step
for(cid in uid){
  dmy <- data[data$id==cid,]
  cll <- apply(dmy[,paste("ll",k,sep="-")],2,sum)
  data[data$id==cid,]$cluster <- which(cll==min(cll))
}
print(c(sum(ll),sum(oll)))
## [1] -429.4164 -429.4164
data$ocluster <- data$cluster

#AIC
aic <- sum(ll)+2*max(k)*5
#BIC
bic <- sum(ll)+max(k)*5*log(nrow(data))

# make new data frame
add_data <- data.frame(clu = kk,
                       aic = aic,
                       bic = bic)
aic_bic <- rbind(aic_bic, add_data)

# sorting
par(mfrow=c(1,max(k)))

# make new data frame
ocluster <- c()
max_len <- c()
clu_max_len <- data.frame(ocluster,max_len)

for(ocluster in k){
  tmp = data[data$ocluster==ocluster,]
  tmp = tmp[tmp$days_from_hatching<300,]
  max_len = max(tmp$fl)
  # make new data frame
  add_data <- data.frame(ocluster, max_len)
  clu_max_len <- rbind(clu_max_len, add_data)
}


# sort by max length
clu_max_len <- clu_max_len[order(clu_max_len$max_len, decreasing=T),]
# create a sequential list
x <- 1:kk
# make new data frame
add_data <- data.frame(x)
names(add_data) <- c("ocluster_rename")
# bind
clu_max_len <- cbind(clu_max_len, add_data)
# merge
data <- left_join(data, clu_max_len, by=c("ocluster"="ocluster"))

# Change the order of the growth curves
# merge a sequential list
estpara2 <- cbind(estpara, x)
# make new data frame
estpara2 <- data.frame(estpara2)
# merge
estpara2 <- left_join(estpara2, clu_max_len, by=c("x"="ocluster"))
# sort
estpara2 <- estpara2[order(estpara2$ocluster_rename),]
# remove columns
estpara2 <- estpara2[,-5]
# convert matrix
estpara2 <- matrix(as.matrix(estpara2), nrow(estpara2), ncol(estpara2))

### plot growth history
kkk <- max(k)
if (max(k) == kk) {
  num_lis <- seq(1,kk,1)
} else {
  num_lis <- seq(1,kkk,1)
}

# plot
# color list
cb = brewer.pal(kk, "RdYlBu")

g <- ggplot(NULL)
for(i in num_lis) {
  # data
  growth_curve <- tibble(
    t = t,
    fl = sbgm(exp(estpara2[i,1]), 
              exp(estpara2[i,2]), 
              exp(estpara2[i,3]), 
              estpara2[i,4], 
              t=t))
  # plot
  g <- g +
    geom_point(data = data[data$ocluster_rename==i,],
               aes(x = days_from_hatching, y = fl), 
               size = 2, alpha = 0.5, fill = cb[i],
               shape = 21, colour = "black") +
    geom_line(data = growth_curve, aes(x = t, y = fl),
              linewidth = 2, alpha=1, col = cb[i]) +
    labs(title = paste0(as.character(i), " clusters"), 
         x = "No. of days since January-1", 
         y = "Fork length (mm)")
}
g

# out to csv
data2 <- aggregate(ocluster_rename~id,data,unique)
write.csv(data2,csv_name, row.names = FALSE)

count(data2, ocluster_rename)

# read data
d0 <- read.csv("./input_data/rawdata_filtered.csv")

# filtering
d1 <- d0 %>% 
  left_join(d_gc, by="id") %>%
  filter(ocluster_rename %in% c(1,2,3)) %>% 
  mutate(growth = as.character(ocluster_rename))

# plot
color_list = brewer.pal(4, "RdYlBu") # color list
color_list = c("#D7191C","#FDAE61","#2C7BB6")

g <- ggplot(NULL) +
  geom_line(data = d1, aes(x = days_from_hatching, y = fl, 
                           group = id, color = growth),
              linewidth = 0.5, alpha=0.8) +
    labs(x = "No. of days since January-1", 
         y = "Fork length (mm)") +
  scale_color_manual('glowth cluster: ', values = color_list) +
  theme(legend.position = 'top')
